en_776190_0	HE the President Maithripala Sirisena, Commander-in-Chief of the Armed Forces coincident with the historic inauguration of the new Army Headquarters on Friday (8) left his signature for promotion of eight senior Brigadiers of the Army to the rank of temporary Major General on the recommendations of the Ministry of Defence and the Commander of the Army, Lieutenant General Shavendra Silva soon after HE the President warmed the new office of the Commander of the Army at the new Army HQ.
en_776190_1	The auspicious gesture, seen as a bonanza given on the inaugural day itself enabled eight most senior Brigadiers in the Army to wear their new ranks, effective from 8 November 2019, the landmark day the New Army HQ was ceremonially opened.
en_776190_2	Here follow the names of newly-promoted Major Generals: Brigadier J.C Gamage of Sri Lanka Engineers, General Officer Commanding, 24 Division.
en_776190_3	Brigadier K.N.S Kotuwegedara of Sri Lanka Artillery, General Officer Commanding, 55 Division.
en_776190_4	Brigadier K.J Jayaweera of Sri Lanka Light Infantry, Commandant, Officer Career Development Centre, Buttala.
en_776190_5	Brigadier K.H.P.P Fernando of Sri Lanka Sinha Regiment, General Officer Commanding, 59 Division.
en_776190_6	Brigadier M.D Wijesundara of Sri Lanka Light Infantry, General Officer Commanding, 66 Division.
en_776190_7	Brigadier A.S Hewawitharana of Sri Lanka Artillery, Director of Military Intelligence.
en_776190_8	Brigadier B.A.L Rathnayake of Sri Lanka Sinha Regiment, General Officer Commanding, 51 Division.
en_776190_9	Brigadier S.S Waduge of Gemunu Watch, General Officer Commanding, 52 Division.
